      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:27",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ أَوْ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ ( عليه السلام ) عَنْ رَجُلٍ أُقِيمَ عَلَيْهِ الْحَدُّ فِي الدُّنْيَا أَ يُعَاقَبُ فِي الْآخِرَةِ فَقَالَ اللَّهُ أَكْرَمُ مِنْ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Zurara, from Humran who said, ",
          "(It has been narrated) ‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> or Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> about a man, upon whom the Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) was established in the world, would he be Punished in the Hereafter?’ So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> is more benevolent than that (to Punish twice)’."
        ]
      }
    }
